text:
Halleck Street, south side, between Henry Street Slip (left) and Columbia Street (right), showing the grain elevator of the New York State Canal Terminal.

October 4, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

Columbia Street, east side, south of Halleck (left) Street, showing at the right background the New York State Canal Terminal Building. The two one story frame shacks at each end are numbered 597 and 601. Halleck Street appears prominently in the foreground.
August 31, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

Columbia Street, south from Halleck Street to Gowanus Canal, showing the New York State Canal Terminal Grain Elevator on the left.
August 31, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
